    3 => '<p>The KAKANDE MINISTRIES is an organization which has a church, a video production studio, hotel. They have a high electricity consumption and were looking for a solution to reduce they electity bill.</p><p>AG Energies has provided a solar solution without battery which will reduce the eletricty bill for the studio as a pilot.</p><p>A 15KWP solar system was supplied and installed:</p><ul><li>30 PV panels of 545W JA solar</li><li>A Sunsynk 12KW hybrid inverter 3phase</li><li>With all the accessories</li><li>remote monitoring</li></ul><p>AG ENERGIES supplied all the material used in that project from Tanzania and took care of the logistic and did a door to door delivery plus installation.</p>',
    5 => '<p>Design, supply and installation of a 30 Kwp solar system composed of 28 PV panels (JA supplier), 15 batteries (BYD) of 75Kwh and 3 inverters of 8 Kw sunsynk (24 kw total) to able day and night power supply for the whole Hospital. This system was a scale up from an existing system of 9Kwp making a total of 30Kwp. The system can now give enough power day and night for the whole hospital.</p>',
    6 => '<p>Design, Supply and installation of 100KWp solar hybrid system with a 100KW inverter and a 200KWH lithium battery bank, 187 PV panels of 545 Watts to power a 100-bed hospital in Kibiti.</p><p>This system powers the whole hospital. Solar is the main source of energy and the Grid serves as back up. They do not use anymore the Generator. This allows them to avoid usage of generator by serving 50% of the cost of running a generator and avoid interruption of power supply during black out.</p>',
    7 => '<p>50KWp grid tie system without Batteries and a 10KW grid tie system without Batteries and PV GENSET Controller.</p><p><em>TENDER</em></p><p>Ifakara Regional Referral Hospital has a hybrid solar power system implemented consisting of a 50KW grid-tied solar system and a 10KW grid-tied solar system. The purpose of this system is to reduce the hospital&#39;s energy consumption during the daytime.</p><p>The system does not include batteries, so the solar power generated during the day is used directly to power the hospital&#39;s electrical loads. During periods of power cuts, a PV GENSET controller helps to reduce fuel consumption by the generator to supply only 30% of it capacity and the rest is supplied by solar.</p><p>This system is able to reduce the hospital&#39;s fuel consumption by up to 50% during periods of power cuts. Overall, the hybrid solar power system is a cost-effective and sustainable solution for reducing energy consumption and providing reliable power&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;hospital.</p>',
    8 => '<p>This was a 20 KWP grid tied solar system with two pieces of 10 KW sun synk invertor, a set of 30 Kwh lithium batteries (liheti) 36PV panels of 545 Watts. 10 kWP system with one 10KW sun synk invertor and 20 Kwh batteries in the surgery ward, 18 PV panels of 545Watts.</p><p>Remote monitoring is done through the symsink app to maximase the use of the solar system. Hybrid inverter on grid and off grid. This system can power the Ultrasound / Lights /Surgery room/ laboratory/maternity Lights / Fridge.</p>',
    9 => '<p>Back up system for the Don Bosco VETA school.</p><p>12KW system composed of 20 PV panels of 545 Watts, 12KW sun synk Inverter, 4 Lithium ion Batteries of 5kwh x 4 A BYD. Day time supply to all campusm and night time power from batterie from 7 pm to 12am. Shifting is done to the grid to keep the batterie reserve.</p>',
    11 => '<p>Since December 2020, the Congregation of Sisters of Mary from the Philippines have inaugurated a 10 000 m2special charity boarding school for 600 girls from poor and less privileged families in Kisarawe in the Archdiocese of Dar es Salaam, Tanzania and 29 teachers. The School offers free secondary education to poor girls from Form 1 to Form 6, with free vocational training and help to seek jobs. Their own green electricity generative system was installed by AG Energies through a 50 KW peak hour on-grid solar system.&nbsp; The system includes 152 PV panels of 325 Watts set on an aluminum roof top frame, a 3 phases 50 KW inverter as well as a Current transformer on each phase to complete the system. Protection against lightning was added through a surge protector. E-distance monitoring was installed through a smart Meter that allows AG Energies to monitor 24/24 the system from Dar es Salaam. Electricity is produced enough for the whole school: All the class rooms, dormitories, kitchen, CCTV Camera system, Water pumps, swimming pool, printing devices, computers, charging plugs.</p>',
    12 => '<p>50 Kwp system, 90 panels of 545watts, 1 grid tie inverter of 50Kw without batterie. This system works only during day time to power all the running machines of the mining and the office appliances&hellip;.</p>',
    13 => '<p>AG Energies answered and won the bid ITB/CANTZ/SIR/2021/01 of CAN &ndash; Tanzania project N0 81267101 funded by the Germany Government through GIZ and implemented by CAN: &lsquo;Enhancing the role of Solar Irrigation for Poverty Reduction near Mt. Kilimanjaro&rsquo; Project in Mkombozi, Kilimambogo, and Ngosero Village&rsquo;. The contract was signed the 7th of June 2022.</p><p>Two solar irrigation systems were supplied and installed in two villages: Mkombozi and Kilimambogo villages in Hai district, Kilimanjaro region. In Kilimambogo the system includes a 10Hp AC submersible pump with head at 130m depth, an 11.7 Kw peak hybrid invertor and 36 pieces of 325Watts monocristalline PV panels. 24 000 L/hr of water is being pumped. Per day we reach 108 000L of water.</p><p>In Mkombazi, a 7.5 Hp submersible pump with head at 80m depth, a 11 Kwp hybrid invertor and 36 pieces of 325 Watts monocristalline PV panels was installed. The system is giving 24 000 L/ hr, per day we reach a maxium capacity of 108 000L of water per day. Three (3) polytanks of 5000L were installed per village and are filled in one (1) hour.</p><p>Those two pumping systems serve to irrigate 100 ha of fields for farmer groups in each village.</p>',
    15 => '<p>- 27 high-efficiency JINCO SOLAR panels, each generating 620W.<br />- A powerful 15 kW HUAWEI grid-tie inverter.</p>',
    16 => '<p>- 14KWp solar panel system,<br />- 12KW Sunsynk 3-phase inverter,<br />- 6 Sunsynk Lithium-ion batteries, each storing 5kWh.</p>',
    17 => '<p>- 20 Kwp PV Panels&nbsp;<br />- 2 Sunsynk Inverters 8 Kwh each&nbsp;<br />- 6 Sunsynk Lithium Batteries 5 Kwh each&nbsp;</p>',
    18 => '<p>At the Sisters of St. Vincent Pallotti in Morogoro, we&#39;ve brought a new dawn with our 100% off-grid solar system.<br />This life-changing project now powers dormitories, classrooms, sisters&#39; houses, the dispensary, and the lab, ensuring that essential services never go dark.<br /><br />In regions where energy access is a daily challenge, this initiative is more than just a technological advancement, it&#39;s a lifeline.<br />By providing reliable electricity, we&#39;re improving healthcare, enhancing education, and securing a brighter future for everyone here.<br /><br />Solar power isn&#39;t just lighting up rooms; it&#39;s saving lives and giving hope.</p>',
    19 => '<p>𝗘𝗺𝗽𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗺𝘂𝗻𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝗧𝗵𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗴𝗵 𝗥𝗲𝗻𝗲𝘄𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝗘𝗻𝗲𝗿𝗴𝘆</p><p>Welcome to 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗶𝗵𝗼, a vibrant community with hospitals, workshops, schools, farms, and endless potential. This solar project is a game-changer, stabilizing power needs and transforming lives.</p><p>During the summer, when hydropower generation drops due to low water levels, and electricity demand peaks from morning to 6 PM, this community relies heavily on diesel generators to fill the gap. The instability of the grid only adds to the challenge.</p><p>By installing a <strong>𝟮𝟬𝟬𝗸𝗪𝗽 𝘀𝗼𝗹𝗮𝗿 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺</strong>, integrated with their existing <strong>𝟱𝟬𝟬𝗸𝗪 𝗵𝘆𝗱𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿</strong>, <strong>𝟲𝟬𝟬𝗸𝗩𝗔 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝟱𝟬𝟬𝗸𝗩𝗔 𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘀</strong>, and the <strong>𝗴𝗿𝗶𝗱 𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗲𝗿</strong>, we&rsquo;re ensuring reliable and sustainable energy. This system will:</p><ul><li><strong>𝗥𝗲𝗱𝘂𝗰𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗻 𝗱𝗶𝗲𝘀𝗲𝗹 𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘀</strong> during critical hours.</li><li><strong>𝗟𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿 𝗳𝘂𝗲𝗹 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘀𝘂𝗺𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻</strong> and <strong>𝗴𝗿𝗶𝗱 𝗲𝗹𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀</strong>.</li><li><strong>𝗦𝘂𝗽𝗽𝗼𝗿𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗵𝘆𝗱𝗿𝗼 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺</strong> by supplementing power during peak demand.</li></ul><p>This is more than a solar installation; it&rsquo;s a step towards a greener, more resilient future for 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗶𝗵𝗼.</p><p>Stay tuned for more updates on how renewable energy is transforming communities like 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗶𝗵𝗼!</p>',
